rements is a suitable experimental candidate to alleviate\npost-selection-related issues. We also show numerically that a transmon array,\nmodeled by an attractive Bose-Hubbard model, in which local measurements of the\nnumber of bosons are probabilistically interleaved, exhibits a phase transition\nin the entanglement entropy properties of the ensemble of trajectories in the\nsteady state.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 6 Feb 2023 17:09:42 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 27 Feb 2023 10:46:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-28"}
